Procedure.description:
Procedure Purpose: FCI SCAN Setup
Procedure Version: 3 Responsibility: Claudia Tranquilli Last Modified Date: 12.12.2022 Change History:
Version 3: (CT - 12.12.2022) - Updated PAF enum values for MS and REPSEQ.
Version 2: (CT - 22.07.2022) - Procedure updated to update the scan scenario also when FCI is in OBSERVATION mode to update MS and scan pattern. - updated to assign SL/SSL/RS slot depending on instrument mode. - added argument SETUP_WP and updated PAF arguments to enum; removed unused arguments.
Version 1: (CT - 09.02.2022) - System procedure created from sequence described in FOM. Procedure sets up the instrument scan configuration; - Procedure Description field updated according to EUMETSAT template; - Procedure History field erased and restarted from Version 1.
Procedure Objectives:
- This procedure sets FCI Scan configuration in terms of Mission Scenario, REPSEQ and FWP. It can be used also to update MS or REPSEQ and FWP only by setting argument appropriately.
Procedure Overview:
This procedure can perform the following activities: - Checks pre-conditions applicable to procedure execution; - The SL slot is assigned depending on FCI mode: if mode is WAIT, SL will be transferred to slot 1 of SCAE; if mode is OBSERVATION, SL will be transferred to the slot that is not ACTIVE. The SSL slot matches the SL one. - Sets the scan scenation by transferring the SL to the SCAE and uploads the SSL; - Updates the REPSEQ to PF and FCI and FWP parameters Rally and IR Calibration Periodicity.
Procedure Pre-conditions: S/C in FPM/NOM, FCI in WAIT or OBSERVATION mode
Procedure Constraints: None
Spacecraft Configuration: FPM/NOM
Ground Segment Configuration: None
Remarks: The REPSEQ is uploaded to the 1st slot (1 for FCI, 0 for PF) as the 2nd slot is used for transition only.
